In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} with @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @Ground Beef{10%ounce} and a big pinch of salt. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in @Red Cabbage and Carrot Mix{4%ounce}, scallion whites, @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tablespoon}, and @Sesame Dressing{1.5%ounce}. Cook until veggies are softened, beef is cooked through, and sauce has thickened, ~{2-4%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and @Pepper{}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with beef mixture and any remaining sauce from pan. Drizzle with Sriracha mayo. Sprinkle with @Crispy Fried Onions{1} and scallion greens. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.